      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear how heavy and exhausting this feels right now, and I want to validate that your struggle is real and valid. It is incredibly hard to feel like a burden on someone who is already navigating their own complex world, especially when you are trying to be supportive. Please know that your feelings of inadequacy and the weight you carry are understandable reactions to a situation that feels overwhelming.\n\nHowever, I also want to gently remind you that your role as a parent is not defined solely by your ability to fix everything for your daughter or your children. There is a lot of love and care in simply being present, even when you can't do much more than offer a listening ear. Sometimes, the most helpful thing you can do is to acknowledge your own limits and seek support for yourself so you don't burn out.\n\nYou are not alone in this, and there are resources available that can help you navigate these difficult emotions. Please consider reaching out to a mental health professional or a support group who can provide you with the tools you need to manage this stress. You deserve to feel supported and understood, and there are people ready to listen and help you find a path forward.",
